    <string name="howto_compat_title">Android Compatibility</string>
    <string name="howto_compat_desc">The Private DNS method (DoT via ADB) requires Android 9 (Pie) or higher (API 28+).\n\nDevices running Android 8 or lower are not compatible with this method. Use the VPN method (DoH) instead.</string>
    <string name="howto_android11_title">Android 11+ — Wireless ADB</string>
    <string name="howto_android11_desc">Since Android 11, the wireless ADB service uses a random port and requires TLS pairing.\n\nOn recent phones, local ADB auto-connect may not work. The VPN method is recommended on these devices.\n\nOn Android TV boxes, port 5555 usually remains accessible.</string>

